Disclaimer : On Vitros Dry chemistry as per the method instructions ,since Total , Direct and Indirect bilirubin are measured independently it can mean that sum of direct bilirubin and Indirect billrubin may not be exactly equal to Tota! billrubin result. The normally expected variability in the independent measurements of Tbil, BU( Indirect), BC( Direct) will occasionally produce a sum of BU+BC that may be slightly greater or slightly less than (upto +//0.3mg/dl) the TBII, even when the true concentrations of Bu+Bc and tbil are identical. Conjugated Bilirubin in plasma reacts to form the bilirubin/albumin conjugate called as delta bilirubin. Delta bilirubin remains elevated for longer duration. Delta bilirubin remains elevated bong after biliary obstruction ts cleared. Kindly correlate clinically. Checked By : 13323
